	   <tr><td colspan=2>What little I know may not be correct as of right now, but last I heard a weapons delay does not make a pet attack faster, but I do believe that they can do more damage with a weapon. Not that I have tested it, mind you. Maybe I'm misremembering, and the bigger weapons do not slow your pet, but that does not make much sense when I think about it. At any rate the last change I remember is a delay-mod. My pets perform adequately bare-fisted, and if they need some help I either heal or nuke, depending on my mood and the situation. A lv 10 pet can hit magical creatures, and somewhere between lv 12 and lv 16 they start double-attacking. The next one is kick, I think, then dual-wield, but I do not remember the specific levels. Check eq.castersrealm.com for some detailed answers... look in the spell list.<br><br>I also do not buy weapons for my pets, and anyone who considers it is being mislead as to what a magician is all about. I'm not sure what that guy meant by "later levels"; it's obvious that he's very high level from his aptitude and quick answers, but maybe he plays an ogre warrior instead of a magician. I have been known to pass a weapon to my pet when I had a crappy one to spare from loot, and I'm pretty sure he did more damage, but I really wasn't looking. The truth is that your weapons will be substandard for your level, but do you really want to give something valuable to a pet since you will not get it back? As for me, I do not even want to give out a weapon due to the downtime to med up again, but no one accused me of being efficient.<br>&nbsp;<br>www.yegolev.com<br>Ibaler the Valewalker<br>Gaheris</td></tr>
